    "content_hash": "74b214d19915e5ae",
    "department": "Operations",
    "description": "Tempo is a layer-1 blockchain purpose-built for stablecoins and real-world payments, born from Stripe’s experience in global payments and Paradigm’s expertise in crypto tech.\n\nTempo’s payment-first design provides a scalable, low-cost predictable backbone that meets the needs of high-volume payment use cases. Our goal is to move money reliably, cheaply, and at scale. Our north star is simplicity for users: fintechs, traditional banks, merchants, platforms, and anyone else looking to move their payments into the 21st century.\n\nWe're building Tempo with design partners who are global leaders in AI, e-commerce, and financial services: Anthropic, Coupang, Deutsche Bank, DoorDash, Mercury, Nubank, OpenAI, Revolut, Shopify, Standard Chartered, Visa, and more.\n\nWe’re a team of crypto-optimists, building the infrastructure needed to bring real, substantial economic flows onchain. We like to move fast and swing for the fences — join us!\n\nThe Role\n\nWe’re looking for an Executive Assistant to help our leadership team operate smoothly as we scale. This is a hands-on, in-office role combining light office management, executive support, and general strategic, operational support for day-to-day execution.\n\nYou’ll be the connective tissue between people, schedules, systems, and the physical office. The scope is intentionally broad: you’ll own the basics, anticipate needs, and help reduce friction so the team can stay focused on building.\n\nThis is an ideal role for someone who thrives in early-stage environments, enjoys wearing multiple hats, and takes pride in running a tight ship.\n\nResponsibilities\n\n - Help members of the leadership/executive team obtain more leverage in their day -- serve as a first communication stop/gatekeeper as needed.\n\n - Strategic and proactive management of complex and varying day-to-day schedules, using Google Calendar and Google suite.\n\n - Coordinate with external partners (including Paradigm support) on office-related needs.\n\n - Travel coordination -- air, ground, hotel and all accommodations.\n\n - Perform an extensive array of core administrative tasks (e.g., preparing meeting materials, contributing to our internal database, chasing down signatures) and ad hoc special projects.\n\n - Plan and execute both internal and external Tempo meetings and events.\n\n - Ensure the office runs smoothly with minimal overhead as the team grows.\n\n - Help support the Legal and People Teams with building systems and managing workflows.\n\n - Handle expenses, reimbursements, and administrative workflows.\n\n - Prepare meeting materials, track follow-ups, and help push projects across the finish line.\n   \n\nQualifications\n\n - Bachelor’s degree and relevant work experience -- ideally direct executive admin support with experience supporting multiple leaders in early stage or growth-stage startups.\n\n - Evidence of grit: the ability to adapt and overcome in rapidly changing situations.\n\n - Excellent written and oral communication; diplomatic and professional demeanor at all times.\n\n - Fluent in Google office platforms and Microsoft Office, with a proven ability to manage time efficiently and prioritize multiple stakeholders, functions, and tasks.\n\n - High levels of integrity and discretion.\n\nAttributes\n\n - Exceptional team player; people-oriented\n\n - Lots of startup experience\n\n - Great listening skills\n\n - Clear and concise communication, in both 1:1 and public settings\n\n - Precise attention to detail\n\n - Adaptability in rapidly changing circumstances\n\n - Highly curious; fast learner\n\n - An affinity for, or interest in, crypto markets",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
